      "title": "[Boing Boing] Lawsuit claims protein bars have nearly twice the claimed calories",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/david.jpg?fit=1067%2C801&quality=60&ssl=1\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\n<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/13/lawsuit-claims-protein-bars-have-nearly-twice-the-claimed-calories.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Lawsuit claims protein bars have nearly twice the claimed calories\"><img alt=\"Image: David Protein\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"801\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/david.jpg?fit=1067%2C801&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1067\" /></a><p>Trying to shed pounds scoffing those David Protein bars stacked at your local Target? A class-action lawsuit claims that <a href=\"https://www.denver7.com/life/food-and-drink/lawsuit-says-protein-bars-sold-at-target-marketed-as-low-fat-pack-a-lot-more-calories\">the numbers on the nutrition label underestimate how much fat they contain and how many calories you'll consume</a> as a result. </p>\n<p>The law allows the label to be 20% off. &#8212; <a class=\"read-more\" href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/13/lawsuit-claims-protein-bars-have-nearly-twice-the-claimed-calories.html\">Read the rest </a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/13/lawsuit-claims-protein-bars-have-nearly-twice-the-claimed-calories.html\">Lawsuit claims protein bars have nearly twice the claimed calories</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://boingboing.net\">Boing Boing</a>.</p>",
